<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>An elderly man is feared to have drowned after he was pulled unconscious from the water at a popular beach in Sydney's eastern suburbs.</p>

<p>Emergency crews were called to Redleaf Beach in Double Bay shortly before 1pm following reports a man aged in his 60s was found unconscious in the water.</p>

<p>Five ambulance crews and a rescue chopper were called to the scene to treat the swimmer and commenced CPR.</p>

<p>A NSW Ambulance spokesman told Daily Mail Australia said the man was in a critical condition at the scene and has not yet been transported to hospital.</p>

<p>'It appears the patient has suffered a medical episiode in the water,' the spokesman said.</p>

<p>No other information on the man's condition is currently available. </p>

<p>More to come. </p>
